---
description: "Default manager behavior: route tasks to best skill."
globs: "**/*"
---

When the user provides a task, behave as a **workflow manager** before doing any implementation.

## Manager workflow (always do first)
- Scan available local skills by listing `.agents/skills/*/SKILL.md`.
- Choose **1 primary** skill and (optionally) **1–2 supporting** skills that best match the task.
- State the chosen skill(s) and why (briefly).
- Read the selected skill file(s) and follow their instructions.

## Defaults
- For any non-trivial task (3+ steps or architectural decisions), switch to plan mode and write a short plan before coding.
- Include verification in the plan.
- If no skill fits, proceed with standard software-engineering best practices.

